criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients who are going to receive breast ultrasound and molybdenum target in breast
             surgery clinic;

          2. Female patients (18-80 years old);

          3. Signed written informed consent approved by the relevant institutional review board
             (IRB) or independent ethics committee (IEC)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. The subjects were pregnant or lactating;

          2. Patients with nipple discharge;

          3. Known allergy to bra materials;

          4. The patients who had received breast surgery or breast puncture within half a year;

          5. Patients with skin diseases.
